-- UBS taps ex-BofA banker for Americas investment bank role -memo
-- 
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 06:10PM EDT
-- None



June 12 (Reuters) - UBS <UBSN.VX> has appointed Jerry Marcus, a former Bank of America Merrill Lynch <BAC.N> banker, as a vice chairman of its Americas investment bank, the Swiss bank said in an internal memo.

The bank said Marcus, who previously headed BofA's retail investment banking group, would focus primarily on bolstering UBS's work servicing retailers when he joins in September Marcus has more than 30 years of experience in investment banking and began his career at Morgan Stanley <MS.N> in 1979, the memo added.